    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2023-12-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-09-18T20:47:25Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Achieving Choice in Education Act or the ACE Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill modifies provisions of qualified tuition programs (i.e., 529 plans) and provides other tax incentives to promote education.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill expands the definition of &lt;em&gt;qualified higher education expense&lt;/em&gt; to include tuition, books or instructional material, fees, and educational therapies for disabled students. It also increases to $20,000 the limitation on distributions from 529 plans for elementary and secondary school expenses.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Further, the bill provides for an increased gift tax exclusion for contributions to 529 plans and limits tax-exempt bond financing to states that implement school choice laws.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
